title: Java Notes!
excerpt:
X.509 Certificate 
 An X.509 certificate is a digital certificate that uses the widely accepted international X.509 public key infrastructure (PKI) standard to verify that a public key belongs to the user, computer or service identity contained within the certificate.

title: About
content: I have done Master of Computer Applications from IIT Roorkee in 2013. I am currently working as a software engineer in Veritas, Pune, India. My area of expertise include knowledge of security (certificate, communication) domain, implementation of REST based web services using Spring REST (Java) and can handle server-side implementation independently. I am selfmotivated person, and ready to learn new technology stack.
